  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently `fromAddress` and `toAddress` arguments of `trace_filter` work as union, yielding results relating to either set of addresses. It would be useful to have an option to intersect the indexes and narrow down the amount of traces to compute. An example of this would be finding all calls from one set of addresses to another.\r\n\r\nAnother useful thing could another index which allows filtering by call input. Storing four byte function signature would be enough for practical reasons.",
